<th colspan="3" style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; color: black; background-color: lawngreen"><span lang="ru" xml:lang="ru">русский язык</span> (<i><span title="Russian transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">russkiy yazyk</span></i>)</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Pronunciation</th>
<td colspan="2"><span title="Pronunciation in IPA" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_Russian" title="Wikipedia:IPA for Russian">[ˈrusʲkʲɪj jɪˈzɨk]</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Spoken in</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Russia" title="Russia">Russia</a>, countries of the former <a href="/wiki/Soviet_Union" title="Soviet Union">Soviet Union</a>, emigrant communities around the world, notably the <a href="/wiki/UK" title="UK" class="mw-redirect">UK</a>, <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">Germany</a>, <a href="/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israel</a>, the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>, <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a>, <a href="/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Latin_America" title="Latin America">Latin America</a>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Total speakers</th>
<td colspan="2">Primary language: about 175 million<br />
Secondary language: 114 million (2006)<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> to 125 million<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><br />
Total: 300 million</td>
</tr>
